Implemented overlap resolution, interest scoring, and max 10 display limit for AR label system.

Key changes:
1. Fixed OverlapResolver: Corrected coordinate system handling (positions are screen coordinates, not normalized). Added screen bounds enforcement and improved overlap detection with padding.

2. Verified POIScorer: All interest scoring components working correctly - category significance (parks/landmarks highest, civic lowest), distance weighting (midpoint optimal), prominence signals, directional centrality (center of 45° FOV > edges).

3. Verified AROverlayView: Max 10 label display with dynamic reappearance - computed properties ensure labels reappear as device moves/rotates and top 10 changes by score.

4. Added comprehensive tests: 490+ lines covering POIScorerTests (15 tests), OverlapResolverTests (20+ tests), MaxDisplayLimitTests, and CompleteOverlapAndScoringTests with full integration scenarios.

All existing tests remain intact and new tests verify correct behavior of overlap resolution, priority-based positioning, score-based filtering, and dynamic reappearance on device movement.
